y, literary analysis, and cultural critique, Scandalize My Name explores topics as varied as serial murder, reality television, Christian evangelism, teenage pregnancy, and the work of Toni Morrison to advance black feminist practice as a mode through which black sociality is both theorized and made material.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2021) 0aAfrican American womenxPublic opinion. 0aAfrican American womenxSocial conditions. 0aAfrican AmericansxMusicxHistory and criticism. 0aFeminismzUnited States. 0aPopular culturezUnited States. 0aPopular musiczUnited StatesxHistory and criticism. 0aPublic opinionzUnited States. 0aRacismzUnited States. 0aSexismzUnited States. 0aStereotypes (Social psychology)zUnited States. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Ethnic Studies / African American Studies.2bisacsh  aAfrican American Women.  aBlack Feminism.  aBlack Social Life.  aBlack Studies.  aStereotypes.  arepresentation.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertFordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311072901640uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978082327475840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780823274758423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780823274758.jpg  a978-3-11-072901-6  Fordham University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK